Perlego Privacy Policy
Please read this privacy notice carefully as it contains important information on (i) who we are; (ii) how and why we collect, store, use and share personal information; (iii) your rights in relation to your personal information; (iv) how a third party may access your personal information; and (v) how to contact us and/or the ICO if you have a complaint.
We use personal data to provide our ebook services and related content to people who request it, register for it, or access our workspaces or community eReaders through an invitation, and to manage our relationships with those people. Generally, we do not share your information with third parties, but there are some exceptions where we use external service providers to power our operations – some of these are outside the UK/EEA. We are happy to answer your questions about any of this – email us at
help@perlego.com
.
We are registered at the UK Information Commissioner’s Office under number
ZA210414
.
Who we are
Perlego Limited ("Perlego”) collects, uses and is responsible for certain personal information about you, which is referred to as “personal data.” When we do so, we are regulated under data protection laws in the UK and EU. We are responsible as "controller" of that personal information for the purposes of those laws.
The personal information we collect and use
Information collected by us, and how we use it
As part of providing the Perlego service, we collect the following personal information (either when it’s provided to us by you, or when we derive it from your use of the service via cookies or similar technology (for more information please see our cookies notice here
Cookie Settings page
):
Contact details. We use this to communicate with you; to authenticate you when you log in to the service; to help facilitate payments; to manage your referral plan account; and to help resolve account and technical issues experienced while using Perlego. If you sign up to Perlego and don’t complete a subscription, we will use your contact details to encourage you to take out a subscription if you have consented to us contacting you in this way during the sign-up process.
Summaries of conversations. We use this to help resolve account and technical issues experienced using Perlego. Such conversations may be conducted with Perlego employees and/or our support helpdesk and may involve the use of our AI chatbot feature.
Details of your subscription to Perlego. We use this to provide you with the Perlego service, to inform you on our methods of communication, and to calculate payments to our publisher partners.
Your geographical region and IP address. We use this to determine whether we have to charge you sales tax; to help resolve technical and account issues; to determine whether we can give you access to the service or to certain books; and to record, and report to our publisher partners, the usage levels of books.
Transactions you undertake on Perlego. This is to enable us to record, and report to our publisher partners, the usage levels of books; and to display to you transactions you undertake on Perlego.
Your usage of the service. This includes the books you read, your reading interests, annotations, highlights and bookmarks; your preferences for viewing books (e.g., font); the mouse activity and keystrokes in your use of the service; and your search history. We use this to provide you with the service, to recommend books and topics to you, to calculate payments due to our publisher partners, and for security and content protection purposes.
In some cases, your course and university or your employer (depending on whether you have a standard account or organization-based account). We use this as part of our reporting information to our publisher partners, and to authenticate you to the service.
Your name and the information accessed and/or uploaded/embedded by you in a workspace or community eReader you either create or are invited to. We use this to provide you with the service; to monitor user content in accordance with our content guidelines and for security purposes.
Payment Information. We use this to determine whether you have paid to access the service or a book, and to check if you are entitled to a free subscription when you apply for one. We use Stripe as our payment processor.
Marketing preferences. We use this to determine whether and how we communicate with you to promote Perlego.
We gather certain technical information from your use of our website by means of cookies and similar technologies. For more details, please review our
Cookie Settings page
.
Additionally, we use the information for the purposes of research we undertake to understand how people use our service, and the books on it, in order to identify the improvements we can make to the service, how we promote it, and the range of books we offer. The research we produce is on an aggregated basis and does not identify you personally. We use it internally and may also provide it to others. We also use some of the information for the purposes of keeping Perlego and our communications with you secure from unauthorized access and attacks, and for reporting any unlawful activity. We may need to process your information for the purposes of enforcing our terms of use.
If you have previously consented to our processing of your data, you can withdraw that consent at any time. To do so, simply email us at
help@perlego.com
.
If you withdraw your consent and we do not have another legal basis for processing your data, we will stop processing it. However, if we have another legal basis for continuing to process your data, we may do so, in accordance with your legal rights.
Whom we share your personal information with
We routinely share information we collect about you with companies that we use to help us provide and run the Perlego service. We only share your data when it is necessary and aligned with the protections and best practices set out in this Privacy Policy. We use third parties for the following:
Category
Type of Data Shared
Cloud Services
All customer data, including backups and metadata.
Firewall as a Service
IP addresses, access logs, browser information, timestamps, geolocation (if logged).
Abuse Monitoring Services
IP addresses, access logs, browser information, suspicious behavior patterns.
Payment Processing Providers
Name, last name, email, address, country, IP address, billing details, join date, transaction IDs, payment method.
